def length_of_last_word(s):
    return len(s.split()[-1])

Write a function called length_of_last_word(s) that takes one parameter as follows:

Parameters:

  s: a string containing words made up strictly of alphabetical characters and spaces

The function returns:

  An int representing the length of the last word in the parameter string s.

A word is defined as a maximal substring consisting only of non-space characters.

Example:
  Arguments:
    s: "Hello World"

  Returns:
    5

  Explanation:
    The last word is "World", which has a length of 5.
